<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-784-834  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 784 834.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  August 13 1990 v4 n29 p17(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Inadequate financial systems dragged Sandamp;Ls down. (savings and loanindustry) (In Perspective)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Levine, Arnold S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A General Accounting Office study on financial managementconcludes that additional actions are needed to improve federalfinancial management systems.andP;  Legislators and federal executivesneed to know the real financial effects of past decisions and thepotential costs and benefits of alternative actions.andP;  Theeffectiveness of decisions will be affected by the quality of thedata provided by the financial management systems.andP;  A currentdebate centers on the proper focus of financial reform.andP;  Thecreation of a government-wide chief financial officer within theTreasury Department has been proposed.andP;  The Treasury's FinancialManagement Service has accomplished little since 1987; it is toosmall an agency and lacks political clout.andP;  There are few federalagencies that place financial reform as a high priority.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Financial AnalysisComputer SystemsSavings and LoanGovernmentUnited States. General Accounting Office.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>